# KGD Account Tracking — V1 Implementation Plan

> **Paper Plate Manufacturing Business — Digital Notebook + Balance Tracker + Billing App**  
> Stack: Next.js · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · Prisma · PostgreSQL

---

## 1. Product Understanding

This is a **real internal business app** for a small paper plate manufacturing business that currently tracks everything in physical notebooks. The three most painful problems are:

1. Forgetting customer balances / outstanding dues
2. Creating quick bills
3. Checking sales history and inventory

This is **not a fixed-price business**. Rates vary per customer, per season, per market rate, and by relationship. The system must never assume fixed prices and must always allow manual override.

The business sells two product types:
- **Plates** — finished paper plates (various sizes, GSM, colors)
- **Sheets** — raw paper sheets (sold to other manufacturers)

Products vary by: size (10", 14"…), GSM (70, 80, 100, 120, 140…), color (silver, gold, green, multi…), and may be sold in packets or loose.

Customers buy on credit, pay partially, pay late, and pay via UPI/cash/bank transfer. One customer can have multiple contacts and multiple phone numbers.

---

## 2. V1 Scope (Build This)

| Module | What it includes |
|---|---|
| **Auth** | Login with email+password, roles: Admin / Staff |
| **Customers** | Create/edit customer, multiple contacts per customer |
| **Products** | Product catalog — plates & sheets with size/GSM/color |
| **Invoices** | Multi-item invoices, manual rate per line, bill-level discount, remarks |
| **Payments** | Record payments against invoices (partial, multiple, any method) |
| **Customer Ledger** | Per-customer running balance — all invoices + payments |
| **Dashboard** | Total outstanding, recent invoices/payments, today/month sales |
| **Audit Trail** | Created/updated by and timestamps on all key records; change log |
| **Basic Inventory** | Manual stock entries for raw materials; visible stock totals |

---

## 3. Out of Scope for V1

- GST calculation / GST filing
- Automatic inventory deduction from production
- Employee / payroll module
- Expense tracking
- Advanced reports / analytics
- WhatsApp sharing
- PDF export (structure is print-ready, actual PDF export is V2)
- Mobile app
- Complex pricing rules / price lists

---

## 4. Proposed Modules

```
Auth          → login, session, role guard
Customers     → list, create, edit, detail, contacts
Products      → list, create, edit
Invoices      → list, create, detail, print view
Payments      → record payment, payment history
Ledger        → per-customer ledger view
Dashboard     → summary cards + recent activity
Inventory     → manual stock entries, stock summary
Audit Logs    → change history (admin only)
```

---

## 5. Database Schema (Prisma)

### Users

```prisma
model User {
  id           String   @id @default(cuid())
  name         String
  email        String   @unique
  passwordHash String
  role         Role     @default(STAFF)
  isActive     Boolean  @default(true)
  createdAt    DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt    DateTime @updatedAt

  invoices     Invoice[]
  payments     Payment[]
  auditLogs    AuditLog[]
}

enum Role {
  ADMIN
  STAFF
}
```

---

### Customers & Contacts

```prisma
model Customer {
  id              String    @id @default(cuid())
  name            String
  businessName    String?
  address         String?
  city            String?
  notes           String?
  defaultDiscount Decimal?  @db.Decimal(5, 2)  // optional % discount suggestion
  isActive        Boolean   @default(true)
  createdAt       DateTime  @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime  @updatedAt
  createdById     String

  contacts        CustomerContact[]
  invoices        Invoice[]
  payments        Payment[]
}

model CustomerContact {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  customerId  String
  name        String
  phone       String?
  role        String?  // e.g. "Owner", "Manager"
  isPrimary   Boolean  @default(false)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())

  customer    Customer @relation(fields: [customerId], references: [id])
}
```

---

### Products

```prisma
model Product {
  id           String      @id @default(cuid())
  name         String      // e.g. "10 inch Silver Plate"
  type         ProductType
  sizeInches   Decimal?    @db.Decimal(5, 2)
  gsm          Int?
  color        String?
  unitLabel    String      @default("packet") // "packet" | "piece" | "kg" | "sheet"
  defaultRate  Decimal?    @db.Decimal(10, 2) // suggested rate, always overridable
  description  String?
  isActive     Boolean     @default(true)
  createdAt    DateTime    @default(now())
  updatedAt    DateTime    @updatedAt

  invoiceItems InvoiceItem[]
}

enum ProductType {
  PLATE
  SHEET
}
```

---

### Invoices & Line Items

```prisma
model Invoice {
  id              String        @id @default(cuid())
  invoiceNumber   String        @unique  // e.g. KGD-2024-001
  customerId      String
  invoiceDate     DateTime      @default(now())
  dueDate         DateTime?
  subtotal        Decimal       @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  discountAmount  Decimal       @default(0) @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  totalAmount     Decimal       @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  paidAmount      Decimal       @default(0) @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  balanceDue      Decimal       @db.Decimal(12, 2)   // computed: totalAmount - paidAmount
  status          InvoiceStatus @default(UNPAID)
  remarks         String?
  createdById     String
  createdAt       DateTime      @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime      @updatedAt

  customer        Customer      @relation(fields: [customerId], references: [id])
  createdBy       User          @relation(fields: [createdById], references: [id])
  items           InvoiceItem[]
  payments        PaymentAllocation[]
}

model InvoiceItem {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  invoiceId   String
  productId   String?  // nullable — allows free-text manual line items
  description String   // always stored for display (auto-filled or manual)
  quantity    Decimal  @db.Decimal(10, 3)
  unit        String   @default("packet")
  rate        Decimal  @db.Decimal(10, 2)   // ALWAYS manually entered / overridable
  amount      Decimal  @db.Decimal(12, 2)   // quantity × rate
  remarks     String?
  sortOrder   Int      @default(0)

  invoice     Invoice  @relation(fields: [invoiceId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  product     Product? @relation(fields: [productId], references: [id])
}

enum InvoiceStatus {
  UNPAID
  PARTIAL
  PAID
  CANCELLED
}
```

---

### Payments & Allocations

```prisma
model Payment {
  id            String        @id @default(cuid())
  customerId    String
  amount        Decimal       @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  paymentDate   DateTime      @default(now())
  method        PaymentMethod @default(CASH)
  reference     String?       // UPI txn ID, cheque number, etc.
  notes         String?
  createdById   String
  createdAt     DateTime      @default(now())

  customer      Customer      @relation(fields: [customerId], references: [id])
  createdBy     User          @relation(fields: [createdById], references: [id])
  allocations   PaymentAllocation[]
}

// Links one payment to one or more invoices
model PaymentAllocation {
  id          String  @id @default(cuid())
  paymentId   String
  invoiceId   String
  amount      Decimal @db.Decimal(12, 2)

  payment     Payment @relation(fields: [paymentId], references: [id])
  invoice     Invoice @relation(fields: [invoiceId], references: [id])
}

enum PaymentMethod {
  CASH
  UPI
  BANK_TRANSFER
  CHEQUE
  OTHER
}
```

---

### Inventory

```prisma
model InventoryItem {
  id           String   @id @default(cuid())
  name         String   // e.g. "Brown Paper 700mm 80GSM"
  category     String   // "RAW_MATERIAL" | "PACKAGING" etc.
  unit         String   // "kg" | "roll" | "piece"
  currentStock Decimal  @db.Decimal(12, 3)
  notes        String?
  isActive     Boolean  @default(true)
  createdAt    DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt    DateTime @updatedAt

  transactions InventoryTransaction[]
}

model InventoryTransaction {
  id              String          @id @default(cuid())
  inventoryItemId String
  type            StockMoveType
  quantity        Decimal         @db.Decimal(12, 3)
  rate            Decimal?        @db.Decimal(10, 2)
  totalCost       Decimal?        @db.Decimal(12, 2)
  transactionDate DateTime        @default(now())
  notes           String?
  createdById     String
  createdAt       DateTime        @default(now())

  item            InventoryItem   @relation(fields: [inventoryItemId], references: [id])
}

enum StockMoveType {
  PURCHASE     // stock came in
  ADJUSTMENT   // manual correction
  SALE         // stock went out (manual)
}
```

---

### Audit Logs

```prisma
model AuditLog {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  entity      String   // "Invoice", "Payment", "Customer", etc.
  entityId    String
  action      String   // "CREATE", "UPDATE", "DELETE"
  oldValues   Json?    // previous state snapshot
  newValues   Json?    // new state snapshot
  performedBy String   // userId
  performedAt DateTime @default(now())
  ipAddress   String?

  user        User     @relation(fields: [performedBy], references: [id])
}
```

