## 7. Implementation Order

| Phase | What | Why |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Project setup + Prisma schema + DB | Foundation first |
| 2 | Auth (login, session, middleware) | Everything gates on this |
| 3 | Customers + Contacts | Core entity |
| 4 | Products | Needed for invoices |
| 5 | Invoices (create, list, detail) | Core billing — the most important flow |
| 6 | Payments (record, list) | Complete the money loop |
| 7 | Customer Ledger | Shows running balance |
| 8 | Dashboard | Brings it all together |
| 9 | Audit Trail | Add last, touches all entities |
| 10 | Basic Inventory | Lower priority but included in V1 |
| 11 | Invoice Print View | Polish for demo |
| 12 | Final testing + walkthrough | Verify end-to-end |

---

## 8. Risks & Edge Cases

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Balance drift — paidAmount on invoice out of sync | Recompute from PaymentAllocations on every payment write |
| Rate changes over time | Rate is stored on InvoiceItem at time of creation, never read from product again |
| Partial payment allocation | Payment can allocate across multiple invoices; track via PaymentAllocation |
| Invoice number collisions | Auto-generate sequential, store uniquely in DB |
| Staff deleting records | Role guard on all delete actions; soft-delete preferred |
| Print layout varies | Start with basic HTML print CSS; proper PDF export in V2 |
| Phone number format | Store as plain string — no validation enforcement, keep flexible |

---

## 9. Clarifying Assumptions Made

1. **GST is not in V1** — fields are present in schema structure but no GST calculation engine
2. **Invoice number format**: `KGD-YYYY-NNNN` (e.g., KGD-2024-0001) — auto-generated
3. **Password auth**: Simple bcrypt email+password login via NextAuth credentials provider (no magic links)
4. **Balance = totalAmount − sum of all PaymentAllocations** — computed in app, stored as a denormalized snapshot on Invoice for fast display
5. **Loose vs packet**: Handled via `unit` field on InvoiceItem (can be "packet", "piece", "kg", "sheet")
6. **Customer-specific pricing**: NOT stored as a price list — just override at billing time with manual entry (per business requirement)
7. **Inventory does not auto-deduct** on invoice creation in V1
8. **Soft deletes**: `isActive` flag used on Customer and Product — never hard delete
9. **Tailwind CSS** via the Next.js default setup (not custom Tailwind config from scratch)
10. **Single currency**: Indian Rupees (₹) — no multi-currency support

---

## 10. Tech Stack Confirmation

| Layer | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 14 App Router | Requested; great for forms + server actions |
| Language | TypeScript | Type safety, better maintainability |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | Fast, clean, non-technical-user friendly |
| ORM | Prisma | Requested; excellent DX + type safety |
| Database | PostgreSQL | Requested; reliable for financial data |
| Auth | NextAuth.js (credentials) | Simple role-based login |
| UI components | shadcn/ui | Clean, accessible, production-ready |

